Pre-Game Insights: The Phoenix Suns finished 49-33 overall and 29-23 in the Western Conference with a strong home record of 24-16. They shot 49.3% from the field and 38.2% from three-point range last season. The Portland Trail Blazers finished 21-61 overall and 8-44 in the Western Conference, giving up 115.4 points per game last season. The Suns and Blazers are set to face each other on November 3, 2024, at 10 p.m. EDT.
